<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-416-566  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 416 566.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telephony  June 26 1989 v216 n26 p13(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>LEC price caps draw big response. (local exchange carrier)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Harper, Maribeth.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Federal Communications Commission's proposal to adopt pricecaps for local exchange carriers (LECs) has been endorsed by theLECs overall, but is encountering opposition from users andinter-exchange carriers.andP;  GTE and Bell regional holding companiesadvocate price caps beginning next year while objecting to the useof an automatic stabilizer or a review period shorter than fouryears.andP;  Southwestern Bell and others state that two years is aninsufficient period to realize the full benefit of price caps.andO;Advocates for small telephone companies stress that exceptionsshould be made for small firms, and both A Tandamp;T and MCI reject theprice-cap plan in its present configuration.andP;  A Tandamp;T argues thatinter-exchange carriers could face higher rates and discriminatorypricing under price caps.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Federal Communications CommissionGovernment RegulationPriceTelephone CompaniesCommon CarriersBell Regional Holding Companies.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>